# Project Structure

my-website/
├── index.html
├── style.css
└── Dockerfile

  
# Sample HTML and CSS Files

  - index.html
    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html lang="en">
    <head>
      <meta charset="UTF-8" />
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
      <title>My Static Site</title>
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
    </head>
    <body>
      <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
      <p>This site is running from a Docker container on AWS EC2!</p>
    </body>
    </html>

  
  - Style.css
      body {
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 50px;
      }
    
      h1 {
        color: #333;
      }


 # Dockerfile       
        FROM nginx:alpine
        COPY . /usr/share/nginx/html

        
 # Deploy on AWS EC2 Ubuntu
  🔸 Step 1: Launch EC2 instance (Ubuntu)
        - Go to AWS → EC2 → Launch Instance → Ubuntu 22.04
        - Allow ports: HTTP (80), HTTPS (443), and SSH (22) in the security group

  🔸 Step 2: Install Docker on EC2

        sudo apt update
        sudo apt install -y docker.io
        sudo systemctl start docker
        sudo systemctl enable docker
        sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu

  🔸 Step 3: Transfer project files to EC2

        sudo apt install git
        git clone https://github.com/your-username/my-website.git
        cd my-website

  🔸 Step 4: Build and Run Docker Image

        cd my-website
        docker build -t static-site .
        docker run -d -p 80:80 static-site

  🔸 Step 5:View Your Website

        Open your browser and go to:
        http://<your-ec2-public-ip>

        You shou ld see your static website!


